# Angeh Quantum Dot Reality Engine - Complete API Reference

## Core Modules

### quantum_dot_4d.angeh

#### Types
- `QuantumDotCore` - 128D quantum state vector with entanglement matrix
- `ProgrammableRealityCell` - QDC cluster with 3D spatial + temporal properties
- `RealitySynthesisUnit` - PRC network with multi-modal output
- `QuantumLoopOrchestrator` - Parallel iteration manager
- `Complete4DQuantumDot` - Full 4-level system

#### Functions

**Level 1: QDC**
```lisp
(qdc-create) → QuantumDotCore
;; Create new Quantum Dot Core with 128D state vector

(qdc-entangle! qdc1 qdc2 strength) → void
;; Entangle two quantum dot cores with specified strength (0.0-1.0)

(qdc-apply-superposition! qdc states weights) → void
;; Apply quantum superposition to QDC with probability amplitudes
```

**Level 2: PRC**
```lisp
(prc-create position shape-type initial-size) → ProgrammableRealityCell
;; Create PRC at position with shape ('string|'emoji|'code) and size (bytes)

(prc-morph-shape! prc new-shape speed) → void
;; Morph cell shape with animation speed (quantum|classical|hybrid algorithm)

(prc-record-modification! prc operation details) → void
;; Record modification in temporal history
```

**Level 3: RSU**
```lisp
(rsu-create) → RealitySynthesisUnit
;; Create Reality Synthesis Unit with output generators

(rsu-synthesize-reality! rsu input-nl) → struct
;; Synthesize all output formats from natural language
;; Returns: {text, code, visual, audio, model-3d}
```

**Level 4: QLO**
```lisp
(qlo-create) → QuantumLoopOrchestrator
;; Create orchestrator with 1M max parallel iterations

(qlo-register-loop! qlo loop) → void
;; Register quantum loop for execution

(qlo-execute-parallel! qlo loop) → any
;; Execute loop with orchestrator management
```

**Complete System**
```lisp
(create-complete-4d-quantum-dot position shape size) → Complete4DQuantumDot
;; Create full 4-level system: QDC → PRC → RSU → QLO

(execute-natural-language nl-input) → struct
;; Complete pipeline: NL → 4D Dot → Multi-Format Output
;; Returns: {dot, text, code, visual, audio, model-3d, latency}
```

---

### quantum_loops.angeh

#### Types
- `QuantumLoopType` - DETERMINISTIC | CONDITIONAL | NESTED | RECURSIVE | INFINITE
- `QuantumLoop` - Loop structure with entangled dots

#### Functions

```lisp
(quantum-loop-create loop-type body range) → QuantumLoop
;; Create quantum loop with automatic optimization

(quantum-loop-deterministic iterations body) → array
;; Execute deterministic loop in O(1) wall-clock time
;; iterations: number of iterations
;; body: function to execute per iteration

(quantum-loop-conditional condition body) → array
;; Execute conditional loop with parallel monitoring
;; condition: function returning bool
;; body: function to execute

(quantum-loop-nested outer inner body) → array
;; Execute nested loops as multi-dimensional tensor
;; outer, inner: iteration counts
;; body: function(i, j)

(quantum-loop-recursive depth base-case recursive-case) → array
;; Execute recursion as quantum tree
;; depth: recursion depth
;; base-case, recursive-case: functions

(quantum-loop-get-stats loop) → struct
;; Get performance statistics
;; Returns: {iterations, instantiation-time, execution-time, merge-time, speedup}
```

---

### parallel_dots_engine.angeh

#### Types
- `NDimensionalDot` - N-dimensional tensor of quantum dots
- `LiveCodingSession` - 4-directional live coding environment

#### Functions

```lisp
(ndot-create dimensions) → NDimensionalDot
;; Create N-dimensional dot (2D to 10D)
;; dimensions: array of dimension sizes [x, y, z, ...]

(ndot-execute-parallel ndot) → struct
;; Execute with GPU/NPU/CPU auto-selection
;; Returns: {device, dimensions, execution-time, result}

(live-coding-session-new) → LiveCodingSession
;; Create 4-directional live coding session

(live-code-natural-language-input! session nl-input) → struct
;; Process NL input with 4-directional streaming
;; Returns: {nl-input, dot-code, execution-result, explanation}
```

