## Core Language Enhancements (v21.1)

### Macro System
Macros allow code transformation at parse/runtime.
```lisp
(def-macro name (params) body)
```
Example:
```lisp
(def-macro unless (condition body)
  (list 'if (list 'not condition) body))
```

### Module Namespacing
Imported modules now maintain their own namespace.
```lisp
(import math)
(math.sin 1.0)
```
Use `(export symbols...)` within a module to expose specific members.

### Standard Libraries (Bridged)
- **`math`**: `sin`, `cos`, `tan`, `sqrt`, `log`, `pi`, `e`, etc.
- **`string`**: `split`, `join`, `replace`, `trim`, `lower`, `upper`, `contains?`, etc.

### Enhanced Error Reporting
The interpreter now tracks filenames and line numbers.
```bash
❌ Error in file.angeh (Line 42, Col 15): division by zero
```

